This paper deals with incentive mechanisms in wireless networks, specifically in cache-enabled small cell networks. The paper uses game theory to model the interactions between the mobile network operator (MNO) and content providers (CPs) in a Stackelberg game. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with pricing and revenue maximization, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory). The paper also uses optimization techniques to determine the optimal price charged by the MNO, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with improving the quality of service (QoS) of users, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with caching mechanisms in wireless networks, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
